<p>I have to 2 databases <code>DB1</code> and <code>DB2</code>.</p>  <p>I have a view called <code>View1</code> which is stored in the database <code>DB2</code>. Now I want to <code>ALTER VIEW</code> from <code>DB1</code> database.</p>  <p>My attempt:</p>  <pre><code>ALTER VIEW DB2..View1  AS     SELECT * FROM DB2..Test; </code></pre>  <p>But I'm getting an error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>'CREATE/ALTER VIEW' does not allow specifying the database name as a prefix to the object name</p> </blockquote>